# What is the significance of Svatove in the conflict?

## Summary
Svatove is a key link in Russian supply lines to parts of occupied Luhansk region <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>, and its loss to the Ukrainian forces has been seen as a major military victory and a sign the war in Ukraine may be entering a new phase <font color=#FF3399>[2, 3]</font>. Its strategic location has been of utmost importance to President Vladimir Putin, as it's recognition of Ukraine's separatist Donetsk and Luhansk People's Republics was the precursor to his invasion of the country in 2014 <font color=#FF3399>[4, 5]</font>. The Ukrainian forces' takeover of Svatove has denied the Russians the possibility of encircling Ukrainian forces in the Donetsk region <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font> and has been seen as a major setback in Putin's goal of seizing control of the two eastern provinces <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>.

